Daly_City.Doelger Building:
The Doelger Building is an 1932 Art Deco office building located in the Inner Sunset district in San Francisco, California. It served as the headquarters of developer Henry Doelger, who built large low-cost housing tracts of San Francisco and Daly City.
In 2013 the Doelger Building became a City of San Francisco Designated Landmark.
